[~tangzhankun], 

1) DevicePluginScheduler: Why use Integer instead int?

2) DeviceMappingManager:
- devicePluginSchedulers: suggest to make it accessed under synchronized, given assignDevices is accessed under synchronized lock. DeviceMappingManager is not used under highly concurrency env. Suggest to make all access to synchronized to simplify logics. 
- 
{code}
312	      // TODO: should check if customized scheduler return values are valid
313	      if (dpsAllocated.size() != count) {
{code} 
Is there any check needed?
- 
{code} 
        // TODO: fall back to default schedule logic?
{code} 
I think your existing throw exception logic is good enough.

[~leftnoteasy], Thanks for the review!
{quote}1) DevicePluginScheduler: Why use Integer instead int?
{quote}
Will change to int.
{quote}devicePluginSchedulers: suggest to make it accessed under synchronized, given assignDevices is accessed under synchronized lock. DeviceMappingManager is not used under highly concurrency env. Suggest to make all access to synchronized to simplify logics.{quote}
Yeah. Add synchronized to "addDevicePluginScheduler". Other access to the hashmap are for testing so don't add the modifier.
{quote}Is there any check needed?{quote}
Here I suggest that do this very basic check because it will report obvious error if some bug exists in the vendor device plugin. And we'll do a out of box tool(YARN-8946) to do more detailed check to ensure it's stateless without running with YARN.
{quote}I think your existing throw exception logic is good enough.{quote}
Ok. Will remove the TODO.

